        "rich_text_8DL9Df": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When shoppers compare precious materials, one question consistently comes up: platinum or diamond which is more expensive? Both are symbols of luxury, rarity, and exceptional craftsmanship, yet their pricing structures differ dramatically. While many assume platinum always costs more because it is a rare metal, others believe diamonds are naturally more valuable due to their desirability and brilliance.</p><p>This guide breaks down the true cost difference between platinum and diamonds, how each is valued, and what you should choose depending on your lifestyle and jewelry preferences.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bUfHBT": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Quick Answer: Diamond or Platinum Which Is More Expensive?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>Quick Answer: Diamond or Platinum Which Is More Expensive?</h1>",
            "custom_id": "quick"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_BCKdYG": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Quick_Answer_Diamond_or_Platinum_Which_Is_More_Expensive.png",
            "text": "<p>In most cases, diamonds are more expensive than platinum, especially when comparing high-quality stones. Platinum is a rare and valuable metal, but diamond prices vary intensely based on the 4Cs cut, color, clarity, and carat. A high-value stone such as a 2 carat diamond typically costs significantly more than the platinum used to mount it.</p><p>However, jewelry design, metal purity, stone quality, and craftsmanship all influence final retail pricing, making a direct comparison more complex.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_JmwFBb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Understanding Platinum and Its Value",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>Understanding Platinum and Its Value</h1>",
            "custom_id": "understanding"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_h6bpmk": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is Platinum?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Is Platinum?</h2>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_DUDbXe": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/What_Is_Platinum.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Platinum is one of the rarest and densest precious metals used in fine jewelry. It is naturally white, hypoallergenic, and extremely durable. Unlike white gold, which requires rhodium plating, platinum retains its color for life, making it a popular choice for high-end <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-ring\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"engagement rings\">engagement rings</a> and everyday jewelry</p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_fAyY4G": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Factors That Make Platinum Valuable",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Factors That Make Platinum Valuable</h2>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
