        "rich_text_iTeW3d": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Diamonds almost always exceed platinum in overall cost when used in fine jewelry designs. A single premium-quality stone can cost more than an entire platinum band.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_33jfEi": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Short-term vs Long-term Value",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Short-term vs Long-term Value</h2><ul><li>Diamonds often retain value when high clarity and color grades are present.<br/><br/></li><li>Platinum provides long-lasting durability and hypoallergenic benefits, appealing to those who want metal that lasts a lifetime.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_JF8Fbk": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Jewelry Type Comparisons",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Jewelry Type Comparisons</h2>",
            "custom_id": "jewelry"
          }
        },
        "image_L4Qjzx": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Jewelry_Type_ComparisonsA.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_aMiy4L": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Jewelry Type Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Platinum Rings vs Diamond Rings</h3><p>A platinum ring without stones generally costs less than a diamond ring. Once diamonds are introduced, especially larger stones or premium cuts, diamonds dominate the pricing.</p><h3>Platinum Band vs Diamond Stud Earrings</h3><p>A simple platinum band is usually more affordable than diamond studs, which rely heavily on carat weight and quality.</p><h3>Complex Designs</h3><p>Jewelry such as a diamond tennis bracelet tends to be significantly more expensive because it contains multiple high-quality stones, unlike a platinum piece that is priced primarily by metal weight.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_xii4nX": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Common Misconceptions Explained",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>Common Misconceptions Explained</h1>",
            "custom_id": "common"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_TTE7Ef": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Common Misconceptions Paragarph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>“Platinum is always more expensive than diamonds.”</h3><p>False. While platinum is rare, diamonds<br/>particularly high-grade stones are far more valuable per unit.</p><h3>“Diamonds are priced by weight like metals.”</h3><p>Incorrect. Diamonds are priced by the 4Cs, not simply by carat weight.</p><h3>“Platinum jewelry costs more purely because of the metal.”</h3><p>Platinum’s density increases cost, but craftsmanship and design also influence final pricing.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bVNEcW": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Common Paragarph2",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>For Budget-Conscious Buyers</h3><ul><li>Choose platinum when the design requires substantial metal weight.<br/></li><li>Choose diamonds cautiously, considering clarity and color to maximize value.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
